	Vigilance Information
	


  PREREQUISITE QUESTION 1:

Does the information suggest that an Accora device has or may have caused or contributed to a death or serious injury?

A serious injury can be an injury or illness that:

- Is life threatening?

- Results in permanent impairment of a body function or permanent damage to a body structure

- Necessitates medical or surgical intervention to preclude permanent impairment of a body function or permanent damage to a body structure

 ${record.custrecord_acc_cc_reportable_pq1}
	  


PREREQUISITE QUESTION 2:

Does the information suggest that the Accora device has:

- malfunctioned (failed to meet its performance specifications or otherwise not perform as intended, due to a product malfunction or from an user error)

- and if the event were to reoccur, would it be likely to cause or contribute to a death or serious injury?

And/or was the same malfunction or misuse of an Accora device previously reported to the FDA, which caused serious injury or death?

 ${record.custrecord_acc_cc_reportable_pq2}



